{"_type":"issue","id":"Elm-2m5","title":"bug: Replace patch stale chars when new content shorter than old","description":"When a text node's content shrinks (e.g. 'Focus: Right' -\u003e 'Focus: Left'), Replace patch Width = newLeaf.Width = 11. Trailer calc uses patchWidth=11 so 11-11=0 trailing spaces. The stale 't' at position 12 is never overwritten. Fix: include OldWidth = oldLeaf.Width in Replace patch; use max(Width,OldWidth) as clearWidth for the trailing space region.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"Jake Hildreth","owner":"93942157+jakehildreth@users.noreply.github.com","created_at":"2026-04-23T19:34:28Z","created_by":"Jake Hildreth","updated_at":"2026-04-24T01:47:15Z","started_at":"2026-04-23T19:34:35Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T01:47:15Z","close_reason":"Fixed via OldWidth/clearWidth/trailer pattern in ConvertTo-AnsiPatch and OldWidth in Compare-ElmViewTree. Committed b475511.","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"Elm-9e2","title":"bug: ConvertTo-AnsiPatch ESC[K erases right-side content in horizontal layouts","description":"Replace patches emit ESC[K (erase to EOL) before writing content. In horizontal row layouts (e.g. ComponentDemo), updating the left component erases right component content on the same terminal row. Fix: remove ESC[K and instead pad content to exact Width with spaces.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"Jake Hildreth","owner":"93942157+jakehildreth@users.noreply.github.com","created_at":"2026-04-23T19:15:40Z","created_by":"Jake Hildreth","updated_at":"2026-04-23T19:18:32Z","started_at":"2026-04-23T19:15:49Z","closed_at":"2026-04-23T19:18:32Z","close_reason":"Closed","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"Elm-s91","title":"feat: five new example demos (Stopwatch, Quiz, ColorPicker, FileExplorer, Snake)","description":"Add five interactive demo scripts to Examples/. Stopwatch: tick-driven timer with lap recording. Quiz: multi-choice Q;\u0026A with scoring. ColorPicker: 256-color palette browser. FileExplorer: Get-ChildItem browser with file details. Snake: playable game with tick-driven loop. Also adds -TickMs to Start-ElmProgram for time-driven demos, fixes Apply-ElmStyle char*int PS5.1 bug, and updates ConvertTo-AnsiOutput cursor tests.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","assignee":"Jake Hildreth","owner":"93942157+jakehildreth@users.noreply.github.com","created_at":"2026-04-24T00:53:23Z","created_by":"Jake Hildreth","updated_at":"2026-04-24T01:43:43Z","started_at":"2026-04-24T01:43:42Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T01:43:43Z","close_reason":"Four demos shipped (Snake removed). Also fixed Copy-ElmModel perf, Apply-ElmStyle PS5.1 compat, terminal driver input responsiveness, and stale-char rendering.","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"Elm-dof","title":"feat: add five example demos (Stopwatch, Quiz, ColorPicker, FileExplorer, Snake)","description":"Add five new example scripts showcasing different capabilities of the Elm module. Stopwatch and Snake require the new -TickMs parameter on Start-ElmProgram for tick-driven state updates. Quiz and FileExplorer show multi-phase views and real PS integration. ColorPicker showcases dense 256-color grid rendering.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","assignee":"Jake Hildreth","owner":"93942157+jakehildreth@users.noreply.github.com","created_at":"2026-04-23T20:32:32Z","created_by":"Jake Hildreth","updated_at":"2026-04-24T01:47:16Z","started_at":"2026-04-23T20:32:37Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T01:47:16Z","close_reason":"Four demos shipped (Stopwatch, Quiz, ColorPicker, FileExplorer). Committed b304f2f.","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"Elm-tal","title":"bug: ComponentDemo no visual gap between Left and Right counters","description":"Invoke-ComponentDemo uses New-ElmRow -Children @(left, right) with no spacer. The two boxes render immediately adjacent with no whitespace between them. Fix: add a spacer New-ElmText node between the two components in the Row.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"Jake Hildreth","owner":"93942157+jakehildreth@users.noreply.github.com","created_at":"2026-04-23T19:15:42Z","created_by":"Jake Hildreth","updated_at":"2026-04-23T19:18:32Z","started_at":"2026-04-23T19:15:50Z","closed_at":"2026-04-23T19:18:32Z","close_reason":"Closed","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
{"_type":"issue","id":"Elm-7uf","title":"fix: remove cursor hide/show from ConvertTo-AnsiOutput","description":"ESC[?25l and ESC[?25h were emitted by ConvertTo-AnsiOutput on every full render, overriding the cursor hide set by Invoke-ElmEventLoop. Removed both sequences from the renderer; cursor visibility is now owned exclusively by the event loop try/finally block.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","assignee":"Jake Hildreth","owner":"93942157+jakehildreth@users.noreply.github.com","created_at":"2026-04-23T13:34:52Z","created_by":"Jake Hildreth","updated_at":"2026-04-23T13:34:59Z","started_at":"2026-04-23T13:34:59Z","closed_at":"2026-04-23T13:34:59Z","close_reason":"Closed","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
